§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ A set $A ∈ 𝗥^n$ is ❬algebraic❭ if there exist polynomials
    $P_1, …, P_n$ such that
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ A = ⋃_{i = 1}^{n} \Set{x ∈ 𝗥^n}{P_i(x) = 0} ⦉
    ⦉⦉

  ‖ In other words, a semialgebraic set can be written as a
    finite union of sets defined by polynomial equations. ⦉
